ell-known images: synagogues and Torah scrolls burning on the night of Kristallnacht; deportations to the ghettos and the camps; and, finally, mass executions in the killing fi elds of Eastern Europe. The unique set of photographs included in On the Death of Jews shows groups of women and children from Liepaja (Liepája), shortly before they were killed in December 1941 in the dunes of Shkede (Škéde) on the Baltic Sea. In the last photograph of the series, we see the victims’ bodies tumbling into the pit.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)vPictorial workszLatviazLiepåaja. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zLatviazLiepājavPictorial works. 0aJewszLatviazLiepājavPictorial works. 0aMassacreszLatviazLiepājavPictorial works. 7aHISTORY / Holocaust.2bisacsh  abaltic region.  aconcentration camps.  adeath camps.  aeuropean history.  afinal solution.  agenocide.  agerman history.  ahistorical photography.  ahistorical photos.  ahistory.  aholocaust studies.  aholocaust.  ajewish persecution.  alatvia.  anazi death squads.  anazi.  aphotoessays.  aphotography.  arare photographs.  awartime atrocities.1 aGlowacka, Dorota, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311099767540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781789208825?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781789208825423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781789208825/original  a978-3-11-099767-5  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK